    def my-old-command [] {}
Use my-new-command instead.

```
’گگعxTitle: title: attr deprecated
Path: Examples
Content:
Add a deprecation warning to a custom command.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> @deprecated
    def outdated [] {}


```
Add a deprecation warning with a custom message.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> @deprecated "Use my-new-command instead."
    @category deprecated
    def my-old-command [] {}
Use my-new-command instead.

```
—ظWarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/attr_deprecated.mdظ@3a20c8717f6fb2d34d2e4162becc3def2c18b5da2f495ea10ee0602f3631ad10¶title: attr deprecated‘¥NotesعBMark a command (default) or flag/switch (--flag) as deprecated. By default, only the first usage will trigger a deprecation warning.
A help message can be included to provide more context for the deprecation, such as what to use as a replacement.
Also consider setting the category to deprecated with @category deprecated
’گگعuTitle: title: attr deprecated
Path: Notes
Content:
Mark a command (default) or flag/switch (--flag) as deprecated. By default, only the first usage will trigger a deprecation warning.
A help message can be included to provide more context for the deprecation, such as what to use as a replacement.
Also consider setting the category to deprecated with @category deprecated
